ublic opinion. It also shows how drama functioned as an integral component of the educational curricula of elite monastic institutions like Tegernsee, where political administrators and diplomats were trained, and how performance served as a common, connective lingua franca among monasteries in twelfth-century Bavaria. In this new translation, Carol Symes provides the first full and faithful rendering of the play’s dynamic language, maintaining the meter, rhyme scheme, and stage directions of the Latin original and restoring the liturgical elements embedded in the text. Kyle A. Thomas, whose fully-staged production tested the theatricality of this translation, provides a new historical and dramaturgical analysis of the play’s rich interpretive and performative possibilities.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAntichristvDrama. 0aChristian drama, Latin (Medieval and modern)vTranslations into English. 4aAntichrist. 4aApokalypse. 4aGeistliches Spiel. 4aMittelalterliches Drama. 4aMittelalterliches Theater. 4aTegernsee. 4atheater and performance studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Drama.2bisacsh  aAntichrist.  aApocalypse.  aMedieval Drama.  aMedieval Liturgical Drama.  aMedieval Theatre.1 aSymes, Carol, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSymes, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThomas, Kyle A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK 